data.text:
All celebrity artists are backed by the amazing Wes Quave 9-piece band!

## Wally Palmer

#### Founding member of The Romantics, with the hit song “What I Like About You”

Wally Palmar, lead singer and founding member of The Romantics, is one of the most recognized vocalists of the 80’s. Singing, playing rhythm guitar, bass guitar and harmonica, Palmar’s unique and memorable musical contributions, have helped The Romantics remain one of the most influential bands emanating from this important period.

## Skip Martin

#### Grammy Award winner of the Dazz Band and 20-year veteran lead singer of Kool & The Gang.

Skip has entertained millions of people around the world as a former lead vocalist for Kool & the Gang and lead vocalist for the Dazz Band, (which won them a Grammy Award for the song “Let It Whip”). His tenor voice has a warm eclectic style developed through the years under the guise of maestro Stevie Wonder.

## Tommy Tutone

#### Tommy Heath, lead singer of the power-pop group Tommy Tutone, with the hit 867-5309

Tommy Tutone, the four-piece power-pop group led by singer Tommy Heath, released a trio of albums in the early ’80s and had a smash hit with “867-5309 / Jenny” in 1982.

## Terri Nunn

#### Multi-platinum recording artist and lead singer of Berlin

A multi-platinum recording artist and mom, Terri started her career as an actress but turned into a music icon, Nunn’s looks and amazing vocal range helped Berlin create a cult following on MTV. In 1986, Berlin topped pop radio around the world with “Take My Breath Away” from the Top Gun soundtrack.

## Mark McGrath

#### Lead singer of Sugar Ray with 10 million records sold worldwide and Two #1 Hits

As lead singer/songwriter for Sugar Ray, McGrath can lay claim to a stunning string of top 10 hits, multiple multi-platinum albums, and countless sold out tours. Mark McGrath has also proven an effervescent and ever-present pop culture personality, with a host of TV, film, and other extracurricular endeavors.
